Detailed Description

Structure of Ethernet QoS rule data

The naming rules on QoS rules are as follows:


1. name="EMS";value="CompanyName/EMSname"

2. name="ManagedElement";value="ManagedElementName"

3. name="QosRule";value="QosRuleName"

The format of QosRuleName is as follows:
"/rack=xx/shelf=yy/slot=zz/qostype£½aaa/qos=nn"

globaldefs::NamingAttributes_T name:
The name of the QOS name. It should be unique networkwide and do not change with T2000 upgrade

string nativeEMSName:
The local name of the QOS fule. It is also the character string showed on T2000 interfaces.

string userLabel:
The user label of the QOS rule. It is also the character string showed on the NMS interfaces.

string owner:
The owner of the QOS rule.

HW_QosType_T type:
The type of the QOS rule.

globaldefs::NVSList_T paraList:
The attribute list supported by the QOS rule. CAR type QoS parameters include Enable, CIR, DCBS, PIR, and DMBS. COS type QoS parameters include costype,and tag priority to user priority mapping.

globaldefs::NVSList_T additionalInfo:
This attribute allows the communication from the EMS to the NMS of additional information which isn't explicitly modelled. It is a readonly attribute.
